# Design Document: Desktop App Enhancements

## Overview

This design covers seven major enhancement areas for the Audira AI Desktop App (Tauri 2 + Next.js 15): real-time animated charts, a full inbox/chat system, an AI agent builder, a visual workflow builder, multi-channel integration, a theme system, and a notification/celebration system.

The architecture builds on the existing foundation:
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 with React 19, framer-motion, recharts, zustand, socket.io-client, tailwindcss
- **Desktop Shell**: Tauri 2 with Rust backend (SQLite, keyring, system tray)
- **Existing Patterns**: Glass-card dark theme, text-[9px]/text-[10px] sizing, zustand stores with persist middleware, socket.io hooks (`useSocket`, `useRealtime`, `useTypingIndicator`)

All enhancements share a common data flow: Socket.IO events → zustand stores → React components with framer-motion animations. The design prioritizes incremental enhancement of existing components over rewrites.

## Architecture

### High-Level System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Desktop["Tauri 2 Desktop Shell"]
        RustBackend["Rust Backend<br/>(SQLite, Keyring, System Tray)"]
    end

    subgraph Frontend["Next.js 15 Frontend"]
        subgraph StateLayer["State Layer"]
            DashboardStore["dashboard-store"]
            InboxStore["inbox-store"]
            AgentStore["agent-builder-store"]
            WorkflowStore["workflow-store"]
            ChannelStore["channel-store"]
            ThemeStore["theme-store"]
            NotificationStore["notification-store"]
        end

        subgraph UILayer["UI Components"]
            Charts["Chart Engine<br/>(recharts + framer-motion)"]
            Inbox["Inbox/Chat System"]
            AgentBuilder["AI Agent Builder"]
            WorkflowBuilder["Workflow Builder"]
            ChannelManager["Channel Manager"]
            ThemeEngine["Theme Engine"]
            NotificationSystem["Notification System"]
        end

        subgraph Hooks["Shared Hooks"]
            UseSocket["useSocket"]
            UseRealtime["useRealtime"]
            UseTheme["useTheme"]
            UseNotifications["useNotifications"]
        end
    end

    subgraph Backend["API Server"]
        SocketServer["Socket.IO Server"]
        REST["REST API"]
        AIEngine["AI Engine"]
    end

    SocketServer -->|events| UseSocket
    UseSocket -->|state updates| StateLayer
    StateLayer -->|reactive| UILayer
    REST -->|data| Hooks
    UILayer -->|commands| REST
    UILayer -->|emit| SocketServer
    RustBackend -->|IPC| Frontend
```

### Data Flow Pattern

All real-time features follow a unidirectional data flow:

1. **Inbound**: Socket.IO event → hook listener → zustand store action → React re-render → framer-motion animation
2. **Outbound**: User action → component handler → zustand action → API call / socket emit → optimistic UI update

### State Management Strategy

Each feature area gets its own zustand store with the following conventions:
- Stores use `persist` middleware for data that survives page reloads (theme, preferences)
- Stores use `subscribeWithSelector` for granular subscriptions (charts, inbox)
- Socket events update stores directly via hook callbacks
- Optimistic updates with rollback on API failure

## Components and Interfaces

### 1. Chart Engine (Real-Time Animated Dashboard)

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/dashboard/
│   ├── animated-stat-card.tsx       # Stat card with counter animation + sparkline
│   ├── realtime-line-chart.tsx      # Live scrolling line chart (messages/min)
│   ├── animated-area-chart.tsx      # Area chart with smooth data transitions
│   ├── activity-pulse.tsx           # Live event frequency indicator
│   ├── live-activity-feed.tsx       # Real-time event feed with fade-in
│   └── chart-skeleton.tsx           # Shimmer loading placeholder
├── hooks/
│   └── use-dashboard-realtime.ts    # Socket subscription for dashboard metrics
└── stores/
    └── dashboard-store.ts           # Dashboard metrics state
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
interface DashboardMetrics {
  totalMessages: number;
  activeConversations: number;
  resolvedToday: number;
  avgResponseTime: number;
  messagesPerMinute: number[];  // last 30 data points
  sparklineData: Record<string, number[]>;  // per-stat 24-point history
}

interface DashboardStore {
  metrics: DashboardMetrics;
  previousMetrics: DashboardMetrics | null;  // for animation interpolation
  isLive: boolean;
  timePeriod: '1h' | '24h' | '7d' | '30d';
  updateMetrics: (partial: Partial<DashboardMetrics>) => void;
  appendActivity: (event: ActivityEvent) => void;
  setTimePeriod: (period: string) => void;
}

interface ActivityEvent {
  id: string;
  type: 'message' | 'conversation' | 'workflow' | 'agent';
  title: string;
  description: string;
  timestamp: string;
  channel?: string;
}
```

**Animation Strategy:**
- `AnimatedCounter`: Uses framer-motion `useSpring` to interpolate between old/new numeric values
- Chart transitions: recharts `<Area>` with `isAnimationActive` + custom `animationDuration={300}`
- Sparklines: Lightweight SVG path with framer-motion `pathLength` animation
- Staggered load: `staggerChildren: 0.1` on dashboard grid container

### 2. Inbox/Chat System

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/inbox/
│   ├── chat-area.tsx                # Enhanced: media, replies, status indicators
│   ├── message-bubble.tsx           # Individual message with status, media, reply
│   ├── media-preview.tsx            # Image thumbnail, doc icon, audio waveform
│   ├── typing-indicator.tsx         # Three bouncing dots animation
│   ├── message-composer.tsx         # Rich input with canned responses, media picker
│   ├── canned-response-dropdown.tsx # Searchable "/" command dropdown
│   ├── message-context-menu.tsx     # Right-click: Reply, Forward, Copy, Delete
│   ├── conversation-list.tsx        # Enhanced: channel badges, typing label
│   ├── conversation-search.tsx      # Full-text search with highlighting
│   ├── assignment-dropdown.tsx      # Agent assignment with workload display
│   ├── contact-detail-panel.tsx     # Enhanced: history, tags, custom fields
│   └── date-separator.tsx           # "Today", "Yesterday", or date label
├── hooks/
│   ├── use-conversations.ts         # Enhanced: search, assignment
│   ├── use-messages.ts              # Message CRUD with optimistic updates
│   └── use-canned-responses.ts      # Canned response fetching/search
└── stores/
    └── inbox-store.ts               # Conversation list, active chat, search state
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
interface Message {
  id: string;
  conversationId: string;
  content: string;
  direction: 'INBOUND' | 'OUTBOUND';
  status: 'PENDING' | 'SENT' | 'DELIVERED' | 'READ' | 'FAILED';
  mediaType?: 'image' | 'document' | 'audio' | 'video';
  mediaUrl?: string;
  mediaThumbnail?: string;
  mediaFileName?: string;
  mediaFileSize?: number;
  replyToId?: string;
  replyToPreview?: string;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}

interface Conversation {
  id: string;
  contactId: string;
  contactName: string;
  contactPhone: string;
  contactAvatar?: string;
  channel: ChannelType;
  status: 'OPEN' | 'PENDING' | 'RESOLVED' | 'CLOSED';
  priority: 'LOW' | 'MEDIUM' | 'HIGH';
  assignedAgentId?: string;
  assignedAgentName?: string;
  lastMessage?: string;
  lastMessageAt?: string;
  unreadCount: number;
  isTyping: boolean;
  tags: string[];
}

type ChannelType = 'whatsapp' | 'telegram' | 'discord' | 'instagram' | 'facebook' | 'email';

interface InboxStore {
  conversations: Conversation[];
  activeConversationId: string | null;
  searchQuery: string;
  channelFilter: ChannelType | 'all';
  messages: Record<string, Message[]>;  // conversationId -> messages
  typingConversations: Set<string>;
  setActiveConversation: (id: string) => void;
  addMessage: (conversationId: string, message: Message) => void;
  updateMessageStatus: (messageId: string, status: Message['status']) => void;
  setTyping: (conversationId: string, isTyping: boolean) => void;
  searchConversations: (query: string) => void;
  filterByChannel: (channel: ChannelType | 'all') => void;
}
```

**Message Bubble Rendering Logic:**
- Direction determines alignment (left/right) and color scheme
- Status icons: `✓` (sent), `✓✓` (delivered), `✓✓` blue (read)
- Media: inline `<img>` with lightbox for images, `<audio>` with custom waveform for audio, file card for documents
- Reply: quoted message snippet with left border accent above the bubble content

### 3. AI Agent Builder

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/ai-agents/
│   ├── agent-builder.tsx            # Main builder layout (form + test panel)
│   ├── agent-config-form.tsx        # Name, personality, system prompt fields
│   ├── agent-knowledge-picker.tsx   # Multi-select knowledge base attachment
│   ├── agent-trigger-editor.tsx     # Keyword/intent pattern configuration
│   ├── agent-response-templates.tsx # Structured reply format editor
│   ├── agent-test-panel.tsx         # Live testing chat interface
│   ├── agent-test-result.tsx        # Response + trigger + sources + confidence
│   ├── agent-performance-cards.tsx  # Metrics: conversations, response time, CSAT
│   ├── agent-language-config.tsx    # Multi-language response templates
│   └── agent-toggle.tsx             # Enable/disable with immediate effect
├── hooks/
│   └── use-agent-builder.ts         # Agent CRUD, testing, metrics
└── stores/
    └── agent-builder-store.ts       # Builder form state, test results
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
interface AIAgent {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  personality: string;
  systemPrompt: string;
  isEnabled: boolean;
  knowledgeBaseIds: string[];
  triggers: AgentTrigger[];
  responseTemplates: ResponseTemplate[];
  languages: string[];
  metrics: AgentMetrics;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}

interface AgentTrigger {
  id: string;
  type: 'keyword' | 'intent' | 'regex';
  pattern: string;
  priority: number;
}

interface ResponseTemplate {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  format: string;  // template with {{variables}}
  language: string;
  queryType: string;
}

interface AgentTestResult {
  response: string;
  matchedTrigger: AgentTrigger | null;
  knowledgeSources: { title: string; relevance: number }[];
  confidenceScore: number;
  responseTimeMs: number;
}

interface AgentMetrics {
  totalConversations: number;
  avgResponseTimeMs: number;
  resolutionRate: number;
  csatScore: number;
}

interface AgentBuilderStore {
  currentAgent: AIAgent | null;
  testMessages: { role: 'user' | 'agent'; content: string }[];
  testResult: AgentTestResult | null;
  isTesting: boolean;
  isDirty: boolean;
  setAgent: (agent: AIAgent) => void;
  updateField: (field: keyof AIAgent, value: any) => void;
  sendTestMessage: (message: string) => Promise<void>;
  toggleAgent: (id: string, enabled: boolean) => Promise<void>;
  saveAgent: () => Promise<void>;
}
```

### 4. Workflow Builder

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/workflows/
│   ├── workflow-canvas.tsx           # Enhanced: drag-drop, zoom, pan, connections
│   ├── workflow-node.tsx             # Draggable node with ports and config
│   ├── workflow-connection.tsx       # Animated SVG bezier connection line
│   ├── workflow-node-palette.tsx     # Sidebar with draggable node types
│   ├── workflow-config-panel.tsx     # Enhanced: node-specific configuration
│   ├── workflow-simulation.tsx       # Test execution with animated path
│   ├── workflow-version-history.tsx  # Version list with restore capability
│   ├── workflow-toolbar.tsx          # Zoom, undo/redo, export/import
│   └── workflow-minimap.tsx          # Overview minimap for large workflows
├── hooks/
│   ├── use-workflow-canvas.ts        # Canvas interactions (zoom, pan, drag)
│   ├── use-workflow-simulation.ts    # Simulation execution logic
│   └── use-workflow-versions.ts      # Version history CRUD
└── stores/
    └── workflow-store.ts             # Graph state, nodes, connections, simulation
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
type WorkflowNodeType = 'trigger' | 'condition' | 'action' | 'delay' | 'split' | 'merge' | 'end';

interface WorkflowNode {
  id: string;
  type: WorkflowNodeType;
  label: string;
  description: string;
  icon: string;
  position: { x: number; y: number };
  config: Record<string, any>;  // type-specific configuration
  inputPorts: Port[];
  outputPorts: Port[];
}

interface Port {
  id: string;
  label?: string;
  type: 'input' | 'output';
}

interface WorkflowConnection {
  id: string;
  sourceNodeId: string;
  sourcePortId: string;
  targetNodeId: string;
  targetPortId: string;
}

interface WorkflowGraph {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  nodes: WorkflowNode[];
  connections: WorkflowConnection[];
  version: number;
  isActive: boolean;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}

interface SimulationState {
  isRunning: boolean;
  currentNodeId: string | null;
  executedNodes: string[];
  executionPath: string[];  // ordered node IDs
  nodeData: Record<string, any>;  // intermediate data per node
  error?: string;
}

interface WorkflowVersion {
  id: string;
  version: number;
  graph: WorkflowGraph;
  author: string;
  timestamp: string;
  description?: string;
}

interface WorkflowStore {
  graph: WorkflowGraph;
  selectedNodeId: string | null;
  simulation: SimulationState;
  versions: WorkflowVersion[];
  zoom: number;
  pan: { x: number; y: number };
  isDragging: boolean;
  draggedNodeType: WorkflowNodeType | null;

  // Node operations
  addNode: (type: WorkflowNodeType, position: { x: number; y: number }) => void;
  moveNode: (id: string, position: { x: number; y: number }) => void;
  deleteNode: (id: string) => void;
  selectNode: (id: string | null) => void;
  updateNodeConfig: (id: string, config: Record<string, any>) => void;

  // Connection operations
  addConnection: (connection: Omit<WorkflowConnection, 'id'>) => void;
  deleteConnection: (id: string) => void;

  // Canvas operations
  setZoom: (zoom: number) => void;
  setPan: (pan: { x: number; y: number }) => void;
  fitToView: () => void;

  // Simulation
  startSimulation: (payload: any) => Promise<void>;
  stopSimulation: () => void;

  // Versioning
  saveVersion: (description?: string) => Promise<void>;
  restoreVersion: (versionId: string) => void;
  exportWorkflow: () => string;
  importWorkflow: (json: string) => void;
}
```

**Canvas Implementation:**
- Custom canvas using absolute positioning + SVG overlay for connections (no react-flow dependency to keep bundle small)
- Drag-and-drop: HTML5 Drag API for palette → canvas, pointer events for node repositioning
- Connections: SVG `<path>` with cubic bezier curves, animated dash-array during simulation
- Zoom: CSS `transform: scale()` on canvas container, scroll wheel handler
- Pan: Pointer drag on empty canvas space, updates `translate()` transform

### 5. Multi-Channel Integration

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/channels/
│   ├── channel-grid.tsx             # Grid view of all connected channels
│   ├── channel-card.tsx             # Status, message count, last activity
│   ├── channel-setup-wizard.tsx     # Step-by-step connection wizard
│   ├── channel-config-telegram.tsx  # Telegram bot token setup
│   ├── channel-config-discord.tsx   # Discord bot setup
│   ├── channel-config-instagram.tsx # Instagram DM API setup
│   ├── channel-config-facebook.tsx  # Facebook Messenger setup
│   ├── channel-config-email.tsx     # SMTP/IMAP credentials setup
│   ├── channel-test-connection.tsx  # Connection verification UI
│   ├── channel-settings.tsx         # Per-channel auto-reply, hours, routing
│   └── channel-error-display.tsx    # Error with troubleshooting steps
├── hooks/
│   └── use-channels.ts              # Channel CRUD, connection testing
└── stores/
    └── channel-store.ts             # Connected channels state
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
interface Channel {
  id: string;
  type: ChannelType;
  name: string;
  status: 'connected' | 'disconnected' | 'error' | 'configuring';
  config: ChannelConfig;
  messageCount: number;
  lastActivityAt?: string;
  errorMessage?: string;
  autoReply?: string;
  businessHours?: BusinessHours;
  routingRules?: RoutingRule[];
}

type ChannelConfig =
  | TelegramConfig
  | DiscordConfig
  | InstagramConfig
  | FacebookConfig
  | EmailConfig;

interface TelegramConfig { botToken: string; webhookUrl: string; }
interface DiscordConfig { botToken: string; guildId: string; channelId: string; }
interface InstagramConfig { accessToken: string; pageId: string; }
interface FacebookConfig { pageAccessToken: string; pageId: string; appSecret: string; }
interface EmailConfig { smtpHost: string; smtpPort: number; imapHost: string; imapPort: number; username: string; password: string; useTls: boolean; }

interface BusinessHours {
  timezone: string;
  schedule: { day: number; start: string; end: string; enabled: boolean }[];
}

interface RoutingRule {
  id: string;
  condition: string;  // keyword or pattern
  assignTo: string;   // agent ID
}

interface ChannelStore {
  channels: Channel[];
  setupWizardChannel: ChannelType | null;
  setupStep: number;
  addChannel: (channel: Channel) => void;
  updateChannelStatus: (id: string, status: Channel['status']) => void;
  testConnection: (id: string) => Promise<boolean>;
  startSetup: (type: ChannelType) => void;
  completeSetup: () => void;
}
```

### 6. Theme System

```
apps/web/src/
├── styles/
│   ├── globals.css                  # Enhanced: light mode variables, transitions
│   └── theme-transitions.css        # Crossfade transition styles
├── components/layout/
│   ├── theme-toggle.tsx             # Dark/light toggle button
│   └── desktop-theme-provider.tsx   # Enhanced: OS preference detection
├── hooks/
│   └── use-theme.ts                 # Theme state, OS preference, persistence
└── stores/
    └── theme-store.ts               # Theme preference with persist
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
type ThemeMode = 'dark' | 'light' | 'system';

interface ThemeStore {
  mode: ThemeMode;
  resolvedTheme: 'dark' | 'light';  // actual applied theme
  isTransitioning: boolean;
  setMode: (mode: ThemeMode) => void;
  toggleTheme: () => void;
}
```

**CSS Variable Strategy:**
- Existing `:root` and `.dark` selectors already define color tokens
- Add `transition: background-color 300ms, color 300ms, border-color 300ms` to `*` selector during theme switch
- Use `prefers-color-scheme` media query for system default
- Theme toggle applies/removes `.dark` class on `<html>` element
- Crossfade: temporarily add `.theme-transitioning` class that enables transitions, remove after 300ms

### 7. Notification & Celebration System

```
apps/web/src/
├── components/ui/
│   ├── toast.tsx                    # Enhanced: types, icons, auto-dismiss, stacking
│   ├── toast-container.tsx          # Positioned container with max 3 visible
│   ├── confetti.tsx                 # Canvas-based confetti animation
│   └── celebration-overlay.tsx      # Milestone celebration with confetti
├── hooks/
│   └── use-celebrations.ts          # Milestone detection and trigger
└── stores/
    └── notification-store.ts        # Toast queue, celebration state
```

**Key Interfaces:**

```typescript
type ToastType = 'success' | 'error' | 'warning' | 'info';

interface Toast {
  id: string;
  type: ToastType;
  title: string;
  message?: string;
  duration?: number;  // default 5000ms
  dismissible?: boolean;
}

interface CelebrationEvent {
  id: string;
  type: 'first_100_messages' | 'first_resolved' | 'first_workflow';
  title: string;
  description: string;
}

interface NotificationStore {
  toasts: Toast[];
  queue: Toast[];  // overflow beyond max visible (3)
  celebration: CelebrationEvent | null;
  soundEnabled: boolean;
  addToast: (toast: Omit<Toast, 'id'>) => void;
  removeToast: (id: string) => void;
  triggerCelebration: (event: CelebrationEvent) => void;
  dismissCelebration: () => void;
}
```

**Toast Stacking:**
- Max 3 visible toasts, positioned bottom-right
- New toasts push existing ones up with framer-motion `layoutId` animation
- Auto-dismiss after 5 seconds with progress bar
- Queue system: when a toast dismisses, next in queue appears

**Confetti:**
- Canvas-based particle system (no external library)
- 150 particles with random colors, sizes, rotation, and gravity
- Duration: 3 seconds with fade-out
- Triggered on milestone achievements detected by `use-celebrations` hook

## Data Models

### Database Schema Extensions (Prisma)

The following models extend the existing Prisma schema:

```prisma
model Channel {
  id            String        @id @default(cuid())
  tenantId      String
  type          ChannelType
  name          String
  status        ChannelStatus @default(DISCONNECTED)
  config        Json          // encrypted channel credentials
  autoReply     String?
  businessHours Json?
  routingRules  Json?
  messageCount  Int           @default(0)
  lastActivityAt DateTime?
  errorMessage  String?
  createdAt     DateTime      @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime      @updatedAt
  tenant        Tenant        @relation(fields: [tenantId], references: [id])
  conversations Conversation[]
}

enum ChannelType {
  WHATSAPP
  TELEGRAM
  DISCORD
  INSTAGRAM
  FACEBOOK
  EMAIL
}

enum ChannelStatus {
  CONNECTED
  DISCONNECTED
  ERROR
  CONFIGURING
}

model AIAgent {
  id              String    @id @default(cuid())
  tenantId        String
  name            String
  personality     String    @db.Text
  systemPrompt    String    @db.Text
  isEnabled       Boolean   @default(false)
  knowledgeBaseIds String[] // references to KnowledgeBase
  triggers        Json      // AgentTrigger[]
  responseTemplates Json    // ResponseTemplate[]
  languages       String[]  @default(["en"])
  totalConversations Int    @default(0)
  avgResponseTimeMs  Int    @default(0)
  resolutionRate  Float     @default(0)
  csatScore       Float     @default(0)
  createdAt       DateTime  @default(now())
  updatedAt       DateTime  @updatedAt
  tenant          Tenant    @relation(fields: [tenantId], references: [id])
}

model Workflow {
  id          String    @id @default(cuid())
  tenantId    String
  name        String
  graph       Json      // WorkflowGraph serialized
  version     Int       @default(1)
  isActive    Boolean   @default(false)
  createdAt   DateTime  @default(now())
